synopsis: After a three month time skip, Rad and Enid come back as a "Tangerine Man" and a mime. While the two display their new prowess, K.O. is upset over the changes and the friends' obvious training blunder. They are quickly put to the test when instead of Boxmore, they face of against Big Blue Demon.
Everyone is forced to deal with some major changes at Boxmore.
When the plaza has its own film festival, K.O., Enid and Rad are sure their entry will win!
Mr. Gar brings in some team building experts to help K.O., Enid and Rad.
K.O., Enid and Rad team up to help Carol out with a special occasion.
Our heroes discover that the Boxmore security camera feed is the most entertaining thing ever.
K.O. tries to help a hero in need and ends up needing some help of his own.
When a new substitute shows up, K.O. and Dendy decide they need to get their old teacher back.
When a Gloop infestation takes over the plaza, Point arrives to contain the situation.
TKO's getting restless.
When Red Action is called to the future for an epic battle, Enid is unsure of what to do.
Dendy and K.O. discover a fun and exciting new POW Card exploit.
Enid and Rad go on a road trip to deliver a package.
When Enid goes to a new school, K.O. sets out to make sure she fits in.
Enid is forced to confront lingering issues from a past friendship.
Lakewood's Megafootball team takes on their rival in a big game.
K.O., Enid and Rad attempt to solve a mystery.

When KO finds himself trapped inside an mysterious place, he encounters other Cartoon Network Heroes (Garnet from Steven Universe, Raven from Teen Titans Go!, and Ben Tennyson from Ben 10) and they band together to escape.

In this crazy Halloween episode, K.O. visits Enid just in time to see her childhood friends from Ghoul School arrive for a visit. The gang is excited to have their "witch" back, but Enid is afraid of telling them about her status as a ninja despite K.O. reminding her that she "had this arc already".

After learning about a secret society within P.O.I.N.T. Prep, K.O., Enid and Rad dig deeper, but are apprehended by the principal, Chip Damage. With Elodie's help, the trio discover that Chip is actually an android created by Dr. Greyman, but his programming seems off.

K.O. finds a bottle of Citrus Twist in the back and summons a sinister genie named Twisty. When she literally answers K.O.'s wish to "make Rad a burger", Enid and K.O. take Twisty to court where they present a series stories Rashomon style.

Carol is called away by Foxtail to protect the glorb tree. Not wanting to leave him with Mr. Gar, K.O. is brought along under the belief that Carol is taking him on a scavenger hunt. It soon becomes apparent that K.O. knows more about Carol's mission than she thought.

An extremely bored Professor Venomous discovers Lord Boxman living in his trash can. Taking pity on him, he lets him stay at his place and quickly finds him annoying. However, Boxman soon comes up with a new scheme to get back at the Bodega that quickly intrigues Venomous and Fink.
